"smart_completions:Untitled Chat 2025-10-15 11-02-51-1760518971544": {"completion":{"request":{"messages":[{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"hey, test?"},{"type":"text","text":"<context>\n<file_tree>\n└── ObsidianMasterThesis/Papers/\n    └── Neuroscience.md\n</file_tree>\n<context_primary path=\"ObsidianMasterThesis/Papers/Neuroscience.md\" mtime=\"6 minutes ago\">\n#### O'Sullivan et al\n\n“How humans solve the cocktail party problem remains unknown. However, progress has been made recently thanks to the realization that cortical activity tracks the amplitude envelope of speech.” \n\n--> has led to regression methods like stimulus reconstruction, but not yet on EEG (only surface recordings and MEG)\n\n--> show that sigle trial unaveraged EEG can be decoded\n--> high correlation\n--> neural processing at 200ms is critical \n\ntimeline:\n1: first discovery - Cherry 1953\n2: changes in cortical activity to track speech stimulus: Ding and Simon 2012, + others\n\t- forward models\n3: backward models: mesgarani and Chang 2012\n4: using EEG: O'sullivan\n\n\n\nDing and Simon MEG\n\n</context_primary>\n</context>"},{"type":"text","text":"hey, test?"}]}]},"responses":[],"chat_model":{"platform_key":"ollama"},"used_context":true},"key":"Untitled Chat 2025-10-15 11-02-51-1760518971544","thread_key":"Untitled Chat 2025-10-15 11-02-51","stream":true,"context_key":"1760519218894","class_name":"SmartCompletion","user_message":"hey, test?","new_user_message":true},
